Application: Warehouse Inventory Manager
  Description: Track products and stock levels across warehouses
Id: 3e157422-d10c-4a2b-b6c3-9f80fc80f27b

--- Identity ---

Users authenticate with stub
Scopes are "inventory.read", "inventory.write", and "inventory.admin"

--- Roles ---

A "warehouse clerk" has "inventory.read" and "inventory.write"
A "warehouse manager" has "inventory.read", "inventory.write", and "inventory.admin"
An "executive" has "inventory.read"

--- Content ---

Content called "products":
  Each product has a SKU which is unique text, required
  Each product has a name which is text, required
  Each product has a description which is text
  Each product has a unit cost which is currency
  Each product has a category which is one of: "raw material", "finished good", "packaging"
  Anyone with "inventory.read" can view products
  Anyone with "inventory.write" can create or update products
  Anyone with "inventory.admin" can delete products

Content called "stock levels":
  Each stock level has a product which references products, required
  Each stock level has a warehouse which is text, required
  Each stock level has a quantity which is a whole number, minimum 0
  Each stock level has a reorder threshold which is a whole number, minimum 0
  Anyone with "inventory.read" can view stock levels
  Anyone with "inventory.write" can create or update stock levels

Content called "reorder alerts":
  Each reorder alert has a product which references products, required
  Each reorder alert has a warehouse which is text, required
  Each reorder alert has a current quantity which is a whole number
  Each reorder alert has a threshold which is a whole number
  Each reorder alert has a created at which is automatic
  Anyone with "inventory.read" can view reorder alerts
  Anyone with "inventory.write" can create reorder alerts
  Anyone with "inventory.admin" can update reorder alerts

--- State ---

State for products called "product lifecycle":
  A product starts as "draft"
  A product can also be "active" or "discontinued"
  A draft product can become active if the user has "inventory.write"
    success shows toast `product.name + " is now active"`
    error shows banner "Could not activate product"
  An active product can become discontinued if the user has "inventory.admin"
    success shows toast `product.name + " has been discontinued"`
  A discontinued product can become active again if the user has "inventory.admin"
    success shows toast `product.name + " reactivated"`

--- Events ---

When `stockLevel.updated && stockLevel.quantity <= stockLevel.reorderThreshold`:
  Create a "reorder alert" with the product, warehouse, current quantity, and threshold

--- User Stories ---

As a warehouse clerk, I want to see all products and their current stock levels
  so that I know what we have on hand:
    Show a page called "Inventory Dashboard"
    Display a table of products with columns: SKU, name, category, status
    For each product, show stock levels grouped by warehouse
    Allow filtering by category, warehouse, and status
    Allow searching by SKU or name
    This table subscribes to stock level changes
    For each product, show actions:
      "Activate" transitions to "active" if available
      "Discontinue" transitions to "discontinued" if available, hide otherwise

As a warehouse clerk, I want to receive stock into the warehouse
  so that inventory levels stay accurate:
    Show a page called "Receive Stock"
    Accept input for product, warehouse, quantity, and reorder threshold
    Create the stock level as a new record
    After saving, return to the Inventory Dashboard

As a warehouse clerk, I want to see all reorder alerts
  so that I can act on low-stock items:
    Show a page called "Reorder Alerts"
    Display a table of reorder alerts with columns: product, warehouse, current quantity, threshold, created at
    Allow filtering by warehouse
    This table subscribes to reorder alerts changes

As a warehouse manager, I want to add new products to the catalog
  so that we can track their inventory:
    Show a page called "Add Product"
    Accept input for SKU, name, description, unit cost, and category
    Validate that `SKU != ""` before saving
    Create the product as draft
    After saving, offer to set initial stock levels per warehouse

As an executive, I want to see an overview of inventory health
  so that I can make purchasing decisions:
    Show a page called "Inventory Overview"
    Display total product count with active vs discontinued breakdown
    Display total stock value `sum(quantity * unit_cost)`
    Show a chart of reorder alerts over the past 30 days

--- Navigation ---

Navigation bar:
  "Dashboard" links to "Inventory Dashboard" visible to all
  "Receive Stock" links to "Receive Stock" visible to clerk, manager
  "Alerts" links to "Reorder Alerts" visible to all, badge: open alert count
  "Add Product" links to "Add Product" visible to manager
  "Overview" links to "Inventory Overview" visible to executive

Stream stock updates and alerts at /api/v1/stream
